<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There are not a lot of hostile takeovers of he=
dge funds. If you run a hedge fund, generally speaking, nobody is going to=
=C2=A0<em>replace=C2=A0</em>you as the manager of that hedge fund without y=
our permission. Your clients might=C2=A0<em>leave</em>, if you underperform=
 or otherwise upset them, but they are not going to come to you as a group =
and say =E2=80=9Cwe got to talking and 51% of us agree that we would rather=
 have Boaz Weinstein run this fund.=E2=80=9D Your lieutenants might become =
dissatisfied with working for you, but generally you control the company an=
d they don=E2=80=99t, so they can=E2=80=99t mount a coup; their only recour=
se is to leave and start their own funds.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But that is because the traditional=C2=A0hedge=
 fund=C2=A0<em>management=C2=A0</em>firm=C2=A0is a=C2=A0private company mos=
tly owned by its founder-boss. You can, however, have a hedge-fund firm tha=
t is also a public company, with public shareholders who control a majority=
 of the votes. Then things can get tricky.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sculptor Capital Management Inc. is a publicly=
 traded hedge-fund=C2=A0firm with about $34 billion of <a href=3D"https://l=
ink.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLm=
dvdi9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTQwMzI1Ni8wMDAxNDAzMjU2MjMwMDAxM=
TEvc2N1LTIwMjMwNjMwLmh0bSNpMDU4MWRhNjhhMWM4NGNkNWJjZDE2NDQ2ODIzMjg4NzRfMTA5=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB48f371b9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> assets under management</a> an=
d an equity market capitalization of about $700 million; it runs multistrat=
egy and credit hedge funds and=C2=A0has a collateralized loan obligation bu=
siness and a real estate private equity business. There is, with Sculptor, =
a lot going on. Some brief highlights:</p>
<ul style=3D"list-style-type: disc; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;">=
=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Daniel Och founded Och-Ziff Capital Ma=
nagement in 1994.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">He=C2=A0<a href=
=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6L=
y93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9BcmNoaXZlcy9lZGdhci9kYXRhLzE0MDMyNTYvMDAwMTE5MzEyNTA3MjQ4=
MjQ1L2Q0MjRiNC5odG0/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB8f227596" itemprop=3D"StoryLin=
k" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-=
decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color:=
 #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">took it publ=
ic in 2007</a>. That is: The=C2=A0<em>management=C2=A0</em>company, the com=
pany that runs the hedge funds, went public; it trades on the stock exchang=
e and=C2=A0public investors can buy its stock. It=C2=A0makes money by charg=
ing management and performance fees on the hedge funds it runs, and shareho=
lders are betting on its continued ability to make those fees. (The funds t=
hemselves are private.)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=E2=80=9CI=
n the late 1990s, [Jimmy] Levin was <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy9jb=
GFzaC1iZXR3ZWVuLWZvdW5kZXItYW5kLXByb3RlZ2UtcGx1bmdlcy1vY2gtemlmZi1pbnRvLWNy=
aXNpcy0xNTE2NzQzOTE2P21vZD1hcnRpY2xlX2lubGluZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBf46=
860fe" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" sty=
le=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width=
: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background=
-color: #ccc;"> working at a summer camp</a> in Wisconsin, teaching Mr. Och=
=E2=80=99s son how to water ski.=E2=80=9D Then Och hired him to work at Och=
-Ziff, took him on as a prot=C3=A9g=C3=A9, and promoted him through the ran=
ks until he seemed likely to be Och=E2=80=99s successor.</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">There was a big bribery scandal that eventually le=
d to settlements with the US <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVh=
c2UvMjAxNi0yMDM/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb064a4c7" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Securities and =
Exchange Commission</a> and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.=
com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuanVzdGljZS5nb3Yvb3BhL3ByL29jaC16a=
WZmLWNhcGl0YWwtbWFuYWdlbWVudC1hZG1pdHMtcm9sZS1hZnJpY2EtYnJpYmVyeS1jb25zcGly=
YWNpZXMtYW5kLWFncmVlcy1wYXktMjEz/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBfd3fa596" itempro=
p=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #=
000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-=
bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"=
> Justice Department</a> in 2016.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">=
Och stepped down in 2019 and the firm <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomber=
gbusiness.com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2N1bHB0b3IuY29tL25ld3M=
vZmlybS1uZXdzLzIwMTktMDktMTItb2NoLXppZmYtY2FwaXRhbC1tYW5hZ2VtZW50LWNoYW5nZX=
MtbmFtZS10by1zY3VscHRvci1jYXBpdGFsLW1hbmFnZW1lbnQvX3Jlcy9pZD1BdHRhY2htZW50c=
y9pbmRleD0wLw/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB6d3d70b8" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" ite=
mscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decora=
tion: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #0000=
00; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> changed its name<=
/a> to Sculptor. Och remains a big shareholder but is no longer directly in=
volved in running Sculptor.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">But fo=
r somewhat mysterious reasons, Och had <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombe=
rgbusiness.com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cud3NqLmNvbS9hcnRpY2xlcy=
9jbGFzaC1iZXR3ZWVuLWZvdW5kZXItYW5kLXByb3RlZ2UtcGx1bmdlcy1vY2gtemlmZi1pbnRvL=
WNyaXNpcy0xNTE2NzQzOTE2P21vZD1hcnRpY2xlX2lubGluZQ/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC=
f46860fe" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" =
style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-wi=
dth: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; backgro=
und-color: #ccc;"> soured on Levin</a>=C2=A0and did=C2=A0<em>not</em>=C2=A0=
hand the firm over to him when he left.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: =
5px;">But in 2020 Sculptor=E2=80=99s board <a href=3D"https://link.mail.blo=
ombergbusiness.com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2N1bHB0b3IuY29tL2=
5ld3MvZmlybS1uZXdzLzIwMjAtMDYtMTAtamltbXktbGV2aW4tdG8tYmVjb21lLWNoaWVmLWV4Z=
WN1dGl2ZS1vZmZpY2VyLW9mLXNjdWxwdG9yLWNhcGl0YWwvX3Jlcy9pZD1BdHRhY2htZW50cy9p=
bmRleD0wL1NDVSUyMC0lMjBQcmVzcyUyMFJlbGVhc2UlMjBKdW5lJTIwMTAsJTIwMjAyMC5wZGY=
/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB2a358f1f" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"ite=
mscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !i=
mportant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bo=
ttom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> made Levin chief executive off=
