ny and its Representatives to not engage further with the Consortium with r=
espect to the Proposal,=E2=80=9D which seems kind of abrupt.</li>=09<li sty=
le=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If I were Weinstein and friends, and I wanted to=
 buy Sculptor, I=E2=80=99d probably want to address the board=E2=80=99s con=
cerns? The amounts of money involved here are just not, to them, all=C2=A0<=
em>that=C2=A0</em>large. This is a club of very wealthy hedge fund managers=
; surely they are good for $650 million.=C2=A0If they need to come up with =
$650 million to pay for Sculptor, and they are pencilling in $260 million o=
f that coming from selling off the CLO business, and Sculptor worries that =
they won=E2=80=99t be able to get that much, the simple answer is for them =
to give Sculptor=C2=A0$650 million of signed equity commitment letters from=
 themselves, try to sell the CLO business, but be on the hook themselves if=
 they can=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0</li>
</ul>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The market is pretty optimistic; at noon today=
 Sculptor=E2=80=99s stock was trading around $11.85, well above the $11.15 =
Rithm deal price.</p>
