<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Goldman Sachs chief executive David Solomon is=
 facing an internal backlash and negative publicity but has for now retaine=
d the backing of the Wall Street bank=E2=80=99s directors and some of its t=
op shareholders.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Solomon is contending with the most challengin=
g period of his nearly five-year tenure as CEO, with the past 12 months pun=
ctuated by falling profits, sagging morale and unflattering press coverage =
=E2=80=94 including a damaging story this month in New York Magazine that a=
sked if he was =E2=80=9Ctoo big a jerk=E2=80=9D to run the bank.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But the board of directors still backs him, an=
d:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">That patience has found support among some of =
the bank=E2=80=99s biggest stockholders. =E2=80=9CWhile David may be unpopu=
lar [among staff], he=E2=80=99s done a solid job as CEO for the shareholder=
s,=E2=80=9D said one top-10 shareholder.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The shareholder jokingly compared the employee=
 rebellion to the Sendero Luminoso =E2=80=94 the Maoist guerrilla group tha=
t terrorised Peru for decades before fading away =E2=80=94 and predicted it=
 =E2=80=9Cmakes a lot of noise [and] peters out eventually, assuming the ba=
nk continues to perform solidly=E2=80=9D.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CObviously he=E2=80=99s not going to b=
e a jerk to the investors. They=E2=80=99ve been much more proactive in talk=
ing to investors than in the past,=E2=80=9D a second top-10 investor said.<=
/p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">In a partnership, =E2=80=9Cbeing a jerk to the=
 investors=E2=80=9D is the same as being a jerk to the (senior)=C2=A0employ=
ees, because the firm is owned by its partners, and if they don=E2=80=99t l=
ike you they can get rid of you. In a public company, those groups are diff=
erent.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergb=
usiness.com/click/32465527.261426/aHR0cHM6Ly9ueW1hZy5jb20vaW50ZWxsaWdlbmNlc=
i9hcnRpY2xlL2RhdmlkLXNvbG9tb24tZ29sZG1hbi1zYWNocy1wcm9maWxlLmh0bWw/607f07ce=
ef4b8524a319a23cBcf02f61e" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" t=
arget=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important;=
 border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-styl=
e: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Jen Wieczner=E2=80=99s profile of Solomo=
n</a> in New York magazine came out while I was on vacation and I am sure y=
ou have already read it but if you haven=E2=80=99t you should, it is amazin=
g. For instance:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Solomon, 61, is bald and broad-shouldered, lik=
e a thicker and more wizened version of Mr. Clean, with eyes so squinted be=
hind doughy features it=E2=80=99s hard to tell what color they are. He walk=
s heavily, a venti iced coffee almost always in hand, as though the sport o=
f being a banker were a physically taxing one. Several years ago, when Gold=
man=E2=80=99s board was auditioning him for promotion to CEO, the bank=E2=
=80=99s image specialists gave Solomon tips on becoming more approachable. =
They suggested that he walk the floors more often and create opportunities =
for small talk =E2=80=94 perhaps by stopping at an assistant=E2=80=99s desk=
 to take a piece of candy.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">=E2=80=9CWhen I told him, =E2=80=98You got to =
stick your hand in the candy bowl,=E2=80=99 he just gave me this look like,=
 Why would I do that? How is that productive?=E2=80=9D recalls the banker. =
The exercise did not succeed in endearing Solomon to the Goldman rank and f=
ile. =E2=80=9CHe would stomp around the floors in a really purposeful way, =
and he=E2=80=99d find the two or three people he knew,=E2=80=9D the banker =
says. =E2=80=9CHe=E2=80=99d knock on their door, and they would get scared.=
 The whole thing didn=E2=80=99t work.=E2=80=9D</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Honestly extremely endearing. That is one mill=
ion percent what I would do if I suddenly became the CEO of an investment b=
ank, just lurch awkwardly between the offices of my friends while trying to=
 look like I knew what I was doing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Also, I don=E2=80=99t know if you knew this, b=
ut every article about Solomon is required to mention his hobby of being a =
DJ, and this one does:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For much of Solomon=E2=80=99s rema=
rkable career, he=E2=80=99s had the financial performance to ignore suggest=
ions that he change his personality. His execution during the pandemic made=
 2021 Goldman=E2=80=99s best fiscal year ever with profits of nearly $22 bi=
llion. Not long afterward, a member of the bank=E2=80=99s board learned he =
was scheduled to=C2=A0play a set at Lollapalooza=C2=A0and confronted him ab=
out the cringey optics. =E2=80=9CListen, this is my hobby. Your hobby is pl=
aying golf,=E2=80=9D Solomon said. The board member tried to sway the CEO: =
=E2=80=9CNo one has ever OD=E2=80=99d at Pine Valley or Shinnecock. There=
=E2=80=99s a reputational thing.=E2=80=9D</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It also quotes former Goldman CEO=C2=A0Lloyd B=
lankfein telling people =E2=80=9CDJ-ing is not a social hobby,=E2=80=9D whi=
ch is not quite true (you=E2=80=99re hosting a party!), but you know what h=
e means: If you go golfing with=C2=A0clients, you spend=C2=A0hours walking =
around and bonding with them; if you DJ an event with clients you have head=
phones on and they can=E2=80=99t talk to you over your sick beats. How can =
you close a deal like that?</p>
